{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8fd12721-e42d-47de-8a23-fb7a6dc0bdde","content":"Since you already have the dump file collected, here's how to analyze it:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n**`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, easiest):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (`printexception`) | Print last exception on current thread |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM crashes) |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch threads |\n\n**Typical workflow to find crash root cause:**\n1. `pe` — check for an unhandled exception\n2. `clrthreads` — find the faulting thread\n3. `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect its call stack\n\n### Alternatives\n- **WinDbg** (Windows) — most powerful, supports SOS extension (`!analyze -v`)\n- **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS) — `plugin load libsosplugin.so`\n- **Visual Studio** — open the `.dmp` file directly for a visual experience\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running `dotnet-dump analyze` on your dump file, or do you need help with a specific tool?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a763eb21-d1de-4b43-bb7b-2fd341d55917","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it. Let me help them with this. I should check if there are any relevant skills available - looking at the available skills, I see \"dump-collect\" but that's specifically for *collecting* dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo I shouldn't invoke the dump-collect skill. Let me provide guidance on analyzing the dump file directly.\n\nI should help them use tools like `dotnet-dump analyze` or `lldb` to analyze the dump. Let me check what tools are available in the environment first.","outputTokens":520},"id":"13d765cd-e2b1-46ab-ac53-be861c24c627","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:08:33.309Z","parentId":"649325ff-854c-4de8-8149-a8f4870c1b71"}
